n his honorable hand in its place, thereby solving the problem that almost caused wars between the Quraysh tribes.We must also point out that Qusayy bin Kilab, one of the ancestors of the Prophet Muhammad, was the first to roof the Kaaba, as he roofed it with duum wood and palm leaves, long before the Quraysh built the Kaaba.\r\n\r\nAbdullah bin Al-Zubair building\r\nDuring the reign of Abdullah bin Al-Zubayr, the Kaaba was rebuilt after it was damaged by the fire that broke out in the Kaaba after it was thrown by a catapult, during the siege of Mecca by Yazid bin Muawiyah in his dispute with Abdullah bin Al-Zubayr. The reason for the siege was that Abdullah bin Al-Zubayr refused to pledge allegiance to Yazid bin Muawiyah and the Zubayrids revolted with him in Medina. So Yazid sent an army to Medina led by Muslim bin Uqba, and entered it and then headed to Mecca, but he died before reaching it, so he was succeeded in commanding the army by Al-Husayn binAl-Numair, who besieged Mecca for a period, and indeed Al-Husayn was able to control Mount Abu Qubais and Mount Qiqaan. Then he began shooting Al-Zubayr and his followers who were holed up inside the mosque with a catapult, and the mosque was hit. Al-Husayn was not satisfied with that, but rather he threw fire at the mosque, causing the Kaaba to burn, and its structure to weaken. However, Al-Husayn returned to the Levant after Yazid died.\r\n\r\nAfter Abdullah bin Al-Zubayr pledged allegiance to the Muslims as Caliph in the year 64 AH, he had two choices before him: either restore the Kaaba or demolish it and then rebuild it. So he decided to demolish the Kaaba and rebuild it on the foundations of the Prophet Abraham, when he had heard from his maternal aunt Aisha, the Mother of the Believers, a hadith in which the Prophet Muhammad said that the Quraysh diminished in building the Kaaba because their wealth fell short of them, and that if the Quraysh had not become new to Islam, he would have rebuilt it and made it hav